title: For Sale/Trade:  1878 Martini Henry Mk II
postcontent: I've got an 1878 dated Martini Henry from the Enfield factory I'm looking to part with. It functions fine but there is an even rust and wear throughout the entire gun. It is missing all sling swivels and it is missing the rear sight. The wood has it's share of chips and splits. I've bought a few "untouched" Martinis from IMA over the years and although this rifle isn't perfect it's in better shape than every untouched Martini I've bought.At some point this rifle saw service in South Australia and is marked as such (SA 2556 on right side of receiver). There are NO Nepalese markings of any kind on this rifle, so this is pre-Nepalese cache and is in considerably better shape than most Martinis available today that came from Nepal (which were stored in shambly piles in a literal castle for over one hundred years before finally being bought by companies in the US to sell to the public).I'm asking $550 but I'd prefer to trade for AKs, AK parts kits, and AK related accessoiries/ammo; particularly 5.45x39 ammo and surplus 5.45 magazines.IMA-USA is selling 1870s dated untouched Martini Henrys they got from Nepal for the same price (www.ima-usa.com/original-british-p-1871-martini-henry-mkii-short-lever-rifle-1870-s-dated-untouched.html) and I guarantee you that the untouched Nepalese rifles they are selling are in considerably worse shape than this rifle.I'm in Oak Harbor and am willing to meet halfway depending on how far out the buyer might be. I have a CPL. This rifle is an antique by law and isn't considered a firearm.HERE IS AN ALBUM OF ADDITIONAL PHOTOS: imgur.com/a/oiO2d
